{"nbformat_minor": 1, "cells": [{"source": ["**\"Women and Children First\"- Assessing if this criteria was followed for survival on the Titanic**\n", "While the Titanic sunk piece by piece,access to life boats was made protitized according to women and children first criteria,in this notebook we analyse the chances that this criteria was followed before anyother like 1st class first and how some other factors got one on the life boat.\n", "First we have two data sets\n", "* the train set\n", "* the test set\n", "We shall use both sets but first lets load them into out workspace."], "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "markdown"}, {"source": ["library(ggplot2) # We shall use this for data visualisation\n", "library(readr) # the read_csv function to load our data into the script\n", "test<-read.csv(\"../input/test.csv\",stringsAsFactors=FALSE) #load the test.csv file\n", "\n", "\n", "#factoring columns in the test.csv\n", "test$Pclass <- as.factor(test$Pclass)\n", "test$Sex <-as.factor(test$Sex)\n", "\n"], "outputs": [], "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "code"}, {"source": ["\n", "\n", "\n"], "metadata": {"_kg_hide-output": false, "collapsed": true, "_kg_hide-input": false, "_cell_guid": "24c9b151-0191-40c7-ba1d-3a9f4c7162d9", "_uuid": "06092b88f614d3db1c399817a2d507af4081efc5"}, "cell_type": "markdown"}, {"source": ["First off we need to know how many people in terms of gender  were aborad the titanic.\n", "This is important in classfying our statement of women and children.We need to know how many women were aboard the titanic compared to men.\n"], "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "markdown"}, {"source": ["#gender distribution on the ship\n", "ggplot(test,aes(x=Sex))+\n", "  geom_bar()"], "outputs": [], "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "code"}, {"source": ["As you can see ,the men on the ship were twice the number of women.but we have to narrow it down to sex by age if we have to cover the for children.so we shall see age distribution by sex."], "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "markdown"}, {"source": ["ggplot(test,aes(Age,fill=Sex))+\n", "  geom_histogram(bins = 10)"], "outputs": [], "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "code"}, {"source": ["So we have tackled the major parts of our title,women and children however we see an arising issue that there were actually more old women on this ship.Well we shall hold on to that til we see if they survived.\n", "However we can ask ourselves since most of the people on this ship were middle aged citzens,lets look into which class they boarded."], "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "markdown"}, {"source": ["#distrubtion of sex by age faceted by class\n", "ggplot(test,aes(Age,fill=Sex))+\n", "  facet_grid(~Pclass)+\n", "  geom_histogram(bins = 10)\n"], "outputs": [], "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "code"}, {"source": ["So we can see that most middle aged people were aboard 3rd class,while 2nd and 1st class were even distributed with even more old people.Most of the children and young people were female.\n", "Now we need to find out if they survived,and what were the chances of survival.\n"], "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "markdown"}, {"source": ["Let us now bring in the second data set that includes survival.This is will be mapped onto our recent data set to see what chances of survival everyone had.First of all how many people survived?\n"], "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "markdown"}, {"source": ["train <- read.csv(\"../input/train.csv\") #load data set\n", "#factoring\n", "train$Survived<- as.factor(train$Survived)\n", "train$Pclass<- as.factor(train$Pclass)\n", "train$Sex<- as.factor(train$Sex)\n", "#how many people survived\n", "ggplot(train,aes(Survived))+\n", "  geom_bar()\n", "\n"], "outputs": [], "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "code"}, {"source": ["We go ahead and see among the survivors how they were broken down into age and sex."], "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "markdown"}, {"source": ["ggplot(train,aes(x= Age,y=Survived,colour= Sex))+\n", "  geom_point() "], "outputs": [], "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "code"}, {"source": ["Lets also look at survival by class.That way we shall conclude if the statement Women and children first was followed regardless other factors like class."], "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "markdown"}, {"source": ["ggplot(train,aes(x= Age,y=Survived,colour= Sex))+\n", "  facet_grid(~Pclass)+\n", "  geom_point()\n", "  "], "outputs": [], "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "code"}, {"source": ["It is right to say that the women and children first criteria was the major criteria followed to save the survivals although more women and children saved were from the 1st and 2nd class.We can digg deeper and findout out more characteristics in this data set.like the female children who didn't survive yet they were in first class,were they aboard with their parents or siblings or a nanny?"], "metadata": {}, "cell_type": "markdown"}], "metadata": {"kernelspec": {"name": "ir", "display_name": "R", "language": "R"}, "language_info": {"name": "R", "pygments_lexer": "r", "mimetype": "text/x-r-source", "file_extension": ".r", "codemirror_mode": "r", "version": "3.4.1"}}, "nbformat": 4}